headline: 'They Want Their Own DoorDash, They're Gonna Be the Ones That Are Paying for It.' Influencer Defends Teaching Money by Making Her Tweens Cover Extras
summary: Popular influencer Jessica Roderick has received a lot of support from her followers for her parenting rule that her 12- and 14-year-old children must pay for their personal purchases. While applying makeup in a TikTok video, Roderick explains that while she covers all family necessities, her two oldest kids are responsible for their wants, such as ordering food from DoorDash and buying things from their Amazon wish lists.
